### Steps table
**![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)**

The **Steps **table lists all individual processing steps that have been executed by the job, and includes the following columns:

**Column**

**Description**

**Icon**

Icon representing the status of the step

**Step**

ID of the step

**Alias**

Name of the step

**Created**

Date and time when the step was created

**Completed**

Date and time when the step was completed

**Duration**

Total duration of the step execution

> Note

The duration is calculated according to the actual execution time, without considering the waiting time for resources or between scheduling and execution.

> Tip

Use the filter buttons to refine the contents of the Steps table:

**Filter**

**Description**

**All**

Displays all steps in the job, regardless of current status

**Executed**

Displays all steps that have been executed by the job, regardless of the outcome status (**Interrupted **and **Completed**)

**In execution**

Displays all steps that are currently being executed by the job

**Suspended**

Displays all steps that have been executed by the job and couldn't be completed (status **Interrupted**)

**Completed**

Displays all steps that have been executed by the job and completed (status **Completed**)

#### Viewing the details of a step
Click on the **Step **ID to view more details on the step.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

> Tip

Click **Download logs **to download the step's logs.

Click **Download content **to download the step's output files.

> Note

If there are multiple files to process on a specific workflow connection, the Batch Workflows multi-instance behavior allows to parallelize the processing of documents within a job to reduce end-to-end time, by running multiple parallel executions with less documents rather than a single execution with a large number of documents.

The individual task executions launched for each step are listed in the **Tasks **table for a specific step.

#### Tasks table
The **Tasks **table lists all individual tasks that have been executed by the step, and includes the following columns:

**Column**

**Description**

**Icon**

**Task**

**Created**

Date and time when the task was scheduled

**Completed**

Date and time when the task was completed

**Duration**

Total duration of the task execution

> Note

The duration is calculated according to the actual execution time, without considering the waiting time for resources or between scheduling and execution.

> Tip

Click on the **Job ID **on the breadcrumb bar at the top to go back to the **Inspect **panel, or click on the **Jobs **link to go back to the main page.

#### Downloading a step's logs
- Move your mouse pointer over the ID of a step, click on the **... **icon that appears.

- Select **Download logs **from the context menu.

> Note

The step's logs are downloaded in plain text format; for example: *bp3.job-11886.step-19098.task-18788.logs*.

> Tip

You may also click on the ID of a step to access its details, and then click **Download logs **to download the step's logs.
